title: Statue of Liberty
image: Statue-large.jpg

description: >

    The Statue of Liberty is a colossal sculpture on Liberty Island in
    New York Harbor, designed by Frédéric Bartholdi and dedicated on
    October 28, 1886. The statue, a gift to the United States from the
    people of France, is of a robed female figure representing
    Libertas, the Roman goddess of freedom, who bears a torch and a a
    tablet evoking the law upon which is inscribed the date of the
    American Declaration of Independence, July 4, 1776. A broken chain
    lies at her feet. The statue has become an icon of freedom and of
    the United States.

